aufman and Marcia S. Ross. For this important work, she is the recipient of the 2023 Brown Democracy Medal from the McCourtney Institute for Democracy, marking the award's tenth year.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aMiddle East Studies. 4aWORLD HISTORY. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Human Rights.2bisacsh  adeath penalty, political prisoner, capital punishment, activism, journalism, gender politics, human rights lawyer.1 aKaufman, Jeff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaranj, Parisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501776120zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501776120zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501776120/original  a978-3-11-075183-3 Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA